                                        <height unit="cm">22.5</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">24.5 (at widest), 17 (at shortest)</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm">8.5</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>
                                    <p>Three lines of fragmentary Latin text, within chiselled border on left side. Chiselled border ends at top and bottom with large dots. Text appears centred on stone, but impossible to confirm without right edge.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote>
                                <p>Text is lightly engraved on stone. Letters have serifs. Serifs on right top of the 'V' in lines 2 and 3 is very pronounced. M in line 2 is oddly shaped and wide (55mm), with a hedera used in place of one of the middle lines.</p>
