            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note>Text after autopsy</note>
                    </app>
                    <app loc="2"><note>A hedera is incorporated into the third stroke of the initial M</note></app>
                    <app loc="3">
                        <note>annis (or annos) is presumably abbreviated, but the precise form would be speculation.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>To the shades of the underworld. Marcus Villius [---] lived for [---] years</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#AA">
                <p>There are no other attestations of this gens in Sicily. Bivona (1994) notes that there was a P. Villius Tappulus who was praetor in Sicily in 203 BCE, but correctly emphasises that this is 'too remote a past to be able to reasonably find a connection between the two'. </p>
            </div>
